Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_sense(25.10)                                              set_sense(25.10)

Name
       set_sense - Selects which phase of the clock to filter at the specified
       point

Syntax
       set_sense

       [-help]

       <pin_or_port_list>

       [-clocks <clock_list>]

       {[-positive | -negative | -stop_propagation ] [-type <type_list> ]}

       Selects which phase of the clock to filter at the specified point.

       This command accepts timing arcs collection as a valid argument.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -clocks <clock_list>
              Specifies  a list of clocks passing through a specified point to
              which the constraint applies.

              When this parameter is not specified,  the  filtering  of  clock
              phase  will be applicable to all the clocks passing through that
              specified point.

              This parameter must be used with a specified pin name and one of
              the parameters : -positive, -negative, or -stop_propagation.

       -negative
              Specifies that positive phase filtered clocks pass through  pins
              in the <pin_list>.

       <pin_or_port_list>
              Specifies the list or collection of cell output pins. The unate-
              ness  specified  by  the  set_sense command is applied to clocks
              propagating through the specified point.

       -positive
              Specifies that negative phase filtered clocks pass through  pins
              in the <pin_list>.

       -stop_propagation
              Stops  the propagation of specified clocks and clock source data
              paths passing through the specified pins.

       -type <type_list>
              Applies  clock  sense  to  object   types   specified   in   the
              <type_list>.  The  type  list  options  are  - all, clock, data,
              clock_source_data, default_data.

              These are explained below:

              * all: Stops all phases from propagating. This is equivalent  to
                specifying both the clock and data options.

              * clock:  Stops  clock  phases launched by clock(s) specified in
                the <clock_list>from propagating.

              * data: Stops all data phases launched by clock(s) specified  in
                <clock_list>,   starting  from  the  pins/ports  specified  in
                <pin_or_port_list>. The objects in the pin_or_port_list can be
                selected anywhere in the design - clock/data network.

              * clock_source_data: Stops only clock source  data  phases  from
                propagating. The combination of clock_source_data and clock is
                equivalent to the existing -stop_propagation option.

              The    -type   parameter   extends   the   capability   of   the
              set_clocks_sense  command  to  selectively  block  data   timing
              phases. This parameter provides a more generalized use model for
              selecting among all types of paths that should be filtered.

              The  -type  parameter  is mutually exclusive with the -positive,
              -negative, and -stop_propagation options.

Examples
              * The following command allows the positive phase clock CLK1  to
                pass  through  CLKBUF1/Z  and  filters  out the negative phase
                clock CLK1:

                set_sense -positive -clocks CLK1 CLKBUF1/Z

              *

                The following command stops clock phases starting from pin1:

                set_sense pin1 -type {clock}

              *

                The following command stops data phases based only on CK1  and
                CK2 starting from pin1:

                set_sense pin1 -type {data} -clocks {CK1 CK2}

              *

                The  following command stops only the clock source data phases
                starting from pin1:

                set_sense pin1 -type {clock_source_data}

              *

                The following command stops the clock and  clock  source  data
                phases:

                set_sense pin1 -type {clock clock_source_data}

                or

                set_sense pin1 -stop_propagation

